If you enter a URI, Confluence automatically make it a link. Sometimes this is not desireable. Sometimes a string that looks like a URI is not a really one, or is not intended to resolve to a resource (an example of this is XML namespace identifiers).

Right now there is no way to indicate that a string (or a whole portion of the document) should not be automatically interpreted for links. There are some workarounds, but they are hacks, such as making the initial h of the string "http://..." to be a character entity or making it uppercase.

